There are also no further fettered exceptions for various indications that exist in many of the more liberal legislation in the world today. For example there are no exemptions based on class, socioeconomic status, health, mental or physical condition of either the mother or child-in-potential.

This creates difficulties for women who otherwise might still want an abortion while feeling outside the norm as far as the law concerns for. It is of utmost importance to also include men and society as a whole in these debates which should not solely focus on religious or political dogma.
